      "description": "Sorcery is the attempt to access and use spiritual power through means other than the revealed and rightful path of relationship with God — through rituals, substances, or alliances with beings other than God. The Hebrew and Greek vocabulary covers both the practice itself and its practitioners. Scripture is consistently and strongly opposed to sorcery throughout both Testaments. The opposition is not because spiritual power is unreal but because accessing it through these means involves alliance with spiritual forces that are opposed to God and destructive to the person who seeks them.",
